<body>
    <div class="container">
        <h1>Gurken-Sanddorn-Ceviche</h1>
        <h2>Frisch & Knackig</h2>

        <div class="ingredients">
            <h2>Ingredients</h2>
            <h3>Leche de Tigre:</h3>
            <ul>
                <li>1 Thai-Chili</li>
                <li>1 red onion</li>
                <li>3 garlic cloves</li>
                <li>50 g ginger</li>
                <li>1 stalk of lemongrass</li>
                <li>50 g fresh turmeric or 1/2 tsp turmeric powder</li>
                <li>125 ml lime juice</li>
                <li>125 ml sea buckthorn juice</li>
                <li>1 tsp salt</li>
            </ul>

            <h3>Ceviche:</h3>
            <ul>
                <li>Salt</li>
                <li>100 g quinoa</li>
                <li>1 cucumber</li>
                <li>1/2 red onion</li>
                <li>1 red chili</li>
                <li>5 dried apricots</li>
                <li>1 tbsp olive oil</li>
                <li>Mint leaves, for garnish</li>
            </ul>
        </div>

        <div class="instructions">
            <h2>Instructions</h2>
            <ol>
                <li>For the Leche de Tigre, remove the seeds from the Thai-Chili. Roughly chop the chili, onion, garlic, ginger, lemongrass, and fresh turmeric (if using). Combine with the lime juice and sea buckthorn juice in a blender, blend until smooth, and strain through a sieve. Let rest for at least one hour.</li>
                <li>For the ceviche, bring a pot of salted water to a boil. Cook the quinoa, reduce the heat, and simmer for about 15 minutes. Drain and set aside.</li>
                <li>Peel the cucumber, slice it lengthwise, and then chop into small cubes. Dice the red onion, chili, and dried apricots into small pieces.</li>
                <li>Combine the quinoa, cucumber, onion, chili, and apricots in a bowl. Drizzle with olive oil, season with a pinch of salt, and mix well.</li>
                <li>Place the ceviche in the center of a plate or bowl, pour the Leche de Tigre around it, and garnish with mint leaves. Serve immediately.</li>
            </ol>
        </div>

        <div class="footer">
            <p>Inspired by fresh and vibrant flavors. Enjoy!</p>
        </div>
    </div>
